{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}
'''International Bodo Festival''' is a traditional festival of the [[Bodo-Kachari people]]. It helds on every year in the different parts of Northeast India. Many tribesman of the '''Bodo race''' performs at this festival. It includes '''Bagurumba dance''' of [[Bodo people]], '''Wangala dance''' of the [[Garo people]] and '''Bohuwa dance''' of the [[Sonowal Kacharis|Sonowals]] etc.

