{{Infobox writer | name = Miquel Hudin | embed = | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = Miquel Hudin.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = Oroville, California, U.S. | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = Wine writer | language = English, Catalan, Spanish | nationality = | ethnicity = | citizenship = American, Croatian | education = | alma_mater = [[University of California, Berkeley]] | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = <!-- or: | notablework = --> | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = {{URL|https://www.hudin.com/}} | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }}
'''Miquel Hudin''' is an American-Croatian wine writer based in [[Catalonia]], [[Spain]].
As a technology entrepreneur, he co-founded [[The Tender]], a local news website for San Francisco's [[Tenderloin,_San_Francisco|Tenderloin]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Hillman|first=Beth|url=http://www.sfweekly.com/culture/meet-your-neighborhood-blogger-miquel-hudin-of-the-tender/|website=SF Weekly|title=Meet Your Neighborhood Blogger: Miquel Hudin of The Tender|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref> as well as [[Maneno]], a non-profit startup focused on creating a platform for news and blogging in Africa, in local languages.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hersman|first=Erik|url=http://whiteafrican.com/2008/11/08/maneno-a-blogging-platform-made-for-africa/|website=White African|title=Maneno: A Blogging Platform Made for Africa|accessdate=2017-01-05}}</ref>
Being a wine lover for years, he saw a lack of approachable, practical wine books, and in response, created a new series called, [[Vinologue]] upon which he currently focuses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scoutmob.com/atlanta/scoutfinds/2339?ref=art_prev|website=Scoutmob|title=Meet Miquel Hudin, Guiding you to your favorite wine|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://vidirecte.cat/noticia/184/entrevista-elia-varela-i-miquel-hudin-autors-de-la-primera-guia-d-enoturisme-de-la-doq-priorat.html|website=Vi Directe|title=Èlia Varela i Miquel Hudin, autors de la primera guia d'enoturisme de la DOQ Priorat|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vinologue.com/about/|website=Vinologue|title=History & About|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref>
==Biography== Originally from the interior of Northern California, Miquel moved to [[San Francisco]] for university and while there, started working for the [[Inglenook_(winery)|Inglenook winery]] in [[Napa Valley]] in 1999.<ref name=about>{{cite web|url=https://www.hudin.com/about/|website=Miquel Hudin|title=About|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref> He worked in various other wine trade capacities including an importer of Central European wines which lead to a growing interest in wine. During this time, he was also involved with the Maneno (2008-2010) and The Tender (2009-2011) [[citizen journalism]] projects.
After traveling extensively around the [[Socialist_Federal_Republic_of_Yugoslavia|Former Yugoslavia]], he founded the Vinologue series in 2008. The premise of the books was to bridge the gap between traditional travel guidebooks and large, glossy wine books to make various wine regions as approachable as possible to wine drinkers of any level.<ref>{{citation|title=Vinologue Priorat|author=Miquel Hudin & Elia Varela Serra|publisher=[[Vinologue]]|isbn=978-1-941-59803-0|year=2015|pages=480|url=http://www.vinologue.com/books/priorat/}}</ref> One of the most recent books in the series he wrote for the [[Priorat_(DOQ)|Priorat]] region in Catalonia received a Gourmand Award in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cookbookfair.com/index.php/gourmand-awards/winners-2014-gg/winners-by-countries-gourmand-awards-2014|website=Gourmand Awards|title=Winners by Country|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref> He is personally active in promoting the quality wines of boutique cellars from both DOQ Priorat as well as [[Montsant DO|DO Montsant]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Asimov|first=Eric|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/28/dining/wine-school-montsant.html|website=New York Times|title=With the Wines of Montsant, It’s All in the Drinking|accessdate=2017-01-05}}</ref>
Since moving to Catalonia, Spain in 2012, he has been a regular contributor to [[Decanter (magazine)|Decanter]], [[The World of Fine Wine]], Harpers Wine & Spirit, Guild of Sommeliers, JancisRobinson.com, and the Catalan language publication, Vadevi.<ref name=writing>{{cite web|url=https://www.hudin.com/writing/|website=Miquel Hudin|title=Writing|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref><ref name=decanter>{{cite web|url=http://www.decanter.com/author/mhudin/|website=Decanter|title=Miquel Hudin, Author at Decanter|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dopenedes.cat/es/actualidad/post.php?s=2016-03-05-nos-visita-miquel-hudin|website=DO Penedès|title=Nos visita Miquel Hudin|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref> He also regularly judges in international wine competitions and leads wine courses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.hvino.com/2016/06/miquel-hudin-leads-georgian-wine.html|website=Hvino News|title=Miquel Hudin leads Georgian wine masterclass in Spain|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.olivardots.com/2015/05/masterclass-de-comparacio-de-terrers-amb-el-periodista-miquel-hudin/?lang=en|website=Olivardots|title=Masterclass of soil comparison with the journalist Miquel Hudin|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dalmacijawineexpo.com/hr/novosti/dwe/miquel-hudin.html|website=Dalmacija Wine Expo|title=Miquel Hudin|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref>
He holds the Certified Sommelier title from the [[Court of Master Sommeliers]] as well as the Certified Sherry Educator.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sherry.wine/trade/sherry-education/sherry-educators|website=Sherry Wines|title=Sherry Educators|accessdate=2017-01-03}}</ref> His wine blog, ''Wine on VI'' was a Finalist for the 2016 Millésima blog awards and in June 2016, he was selected as the recipient of the Geoffrey Roberts Award for a forthcoming book on the wines for the [[Georgia_(country)|Republic of Georgia]]. He was also named "Best Drink Writer of the Year" in the annual Fortnum & Mason Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fortnumandmason.com/events/food-and-drink-awards-2017|website=Fortnum & Mason|title=Food & Drink Awards 2017|accessdate=2017-05-21}}</ref><ref name=geoffrey>{{cite web|last=|first=|url=http://www.geoffreyrobertsaward.com/2016.html|website=Geoffrey Roberts Award|title=2016 Award Recipient|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.harpers.co.uk/news/miquel-hudin-receives-2016-geoffrey-roberts-award-for-book-on-georgian-wine/541875.article|website=Harpers|title=Miquel Hudin receives 2016 Geoffrey Roberts Award for book on Georgian Wine|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref><ref name=millesima>{{cite web|url=http://blog.millesima-usa.com/2016/02/09/2016-blog-awards-finalists/|website=Millésima Blog|title=The 2016 Blog Awards Finalists|accessdate=2016-12-28}}</ref>
